---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredDataAbout from '../components/StructuredDataAbout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About | Abderrahim GHAZALI"
  description="11+ years in software engineering. AI agent development, RAG systems, semantic search, n8n workflow automation, enterprise Drupal architecture, and full-stack development."
  keywords="AI agent development, RAG systems, semantic search, n8n automation, Drupal architecture, LangChain, full-stack developer, workflow automation"
  url="https://abderrahimghazali.github.io/about"
>
  <!-- Nav -->
  <nav class="fade-in flex items-center gap-6 mb-16 text-sm" style="--stagger: 1">
    <a href="/" class="nav-link">home</a>
    <a href="https://github.com/abderrahimghazali" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="nav-link">github</a>
    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/abderrahim-ghazali-5121b855" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="nav-link">linkedin</a>
  </nav>

  <!-- Header -->
  <header class="fade-in mb-12" style="--stagger: 2">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[#111] mb-2">About</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-[#666]">11+ years in software engineering, automation, and enterprise platforms</p>
  </header>

  <!-- Content -->
  <article class="space-y-10">
    <section class="fade-in" style="--stagger: 3">
      <p class="body-text">
        I'm a software engineer focused on building production systems that eliminate manual overhead at scale. My work sits at the intersection of AI engineering, enterprise CMS architecture, and full-stack development. I've delivered solutions across healthcare, publishing, government, and e-commerce.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="fade-in" style="--stagger: 4">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Approach</h2>
      <p class="body-text">
        Every system I design starts with failure analysis: edge cases, security boundaries, scaling constraints, and operational risk. I engineer for the scenarios that surface at 3 AM with no one watching. This defensive-first methodology is what separates production-grade software from prototypes, and it's the foundation of everything I ship.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="fade-in" style="--stagger: 5">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Technical Depth</h2>
      <p class="body-text mb-4">
        Full-stack proficiency across React, Next.js, Node.js, Drupal, Symfony, and Laravel. Database architecture with PostgreSQL and MySQL. Infrastructure and deployment with Docker, CI/CD pipelines, and cloud platforms. I've led performance optimization efforts on high-traffic platforms and integrated AI models into mission-critical production systems.
      </p>
      <p class="body-text">
        Currently focused on AI agent orchestration, RAG systems, semantic search, and autonomous workflow automation with custom n8n pipelines. Building the layer where LLMs, business logic, and existing infrastructure converge into reliable, observable tooling.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact -->
    <section class="fade-in pt-6 border-t border-[#eee]" style="--stagger: 6">
      <p class="body-text mb-6">
        Open to consulting engagements, contract work, and technical collaboration on complex systems.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm">
        <a href="https://github.com/abderrahimghazali" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link-pill">GitHub</a>
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/abderrahim-ghazali-5121b855" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link-pill">LinkedIn</a>
        <a href="mailto:ghazali.abderrahim1@gmail.com" class="link-pill">Email</a>
        <a href="https://www.drupal.org/u/gabderrahim" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="link-pill">Drupal.org</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>

  <StructuredDataAbout />
</Layout>

<script>
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const prefersReduced = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;
    if (prefersReduced) return;
    document.querySelectorAll('.fade-in').forEach(el => {
      el.style.opacity = '0';
      el.classList.add('is-visible');
    });
  });
</script>

<style>
  .nav-link {
    color: #666;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .nav-link:hover {
    color: #111;
  }

  .section-heading {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: #111;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .body-text {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #555;
  }

  .link-pill {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 6px 14px;
    border: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
    border-radius: 6px;
    color: #555;
    font-size: 13px;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
  }
  .link-pill:hover {
    border-color: #111;
    color: #111;
  }

  /* Fade-in: visible by default, animated via JS */
  .fade-in.is-visible {
    animation: fadeIn 0.5s ease forwards;
    animation-delay: calc(var(--stagger) * 0.1s);
  }

  @keyframes fadeIn {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(8px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }
</style>
